FBIS4-27960 "dreas109_d_94009" FBIS-EAS-94-109 Daily Report 7 Jun 1994 South Korea DPRK Foreign Minister Asks U.S. To Negotiate DPRK Foreign Minister Asks U.S. To Negotiate SK0706024494 Seoul KYONGHYANG SINMUN in Korean 7 Jun 94 p 1 SK0706024494 Seoul KYONGHYANG SINMUN Korean BFN [YONHAP report from Kiev] [Text] On 6 June, North Korea stated that sanctions or pressure against it would not be beneficial to resolving the nuclear issue and asked the United States to return to negotiations. North Korean Foreign Minister Kim Yong-nam said this at the Kiev airport. He arrived in Kiev via Turkey to visit Ukraine.
